radiographic_examinations.findings: There is no consolidation at the lung bases. Minimal bibasilar atelectasis at the lung bases. The liver enhances homogeneously. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary duct dilatation. The main portal vein is patent. The pancreas and spleen appear normal. Bilateral thickening in the adrenal glands. The stomach appears normal. No evidence of bowel obstruction. No free fluid or free air. Fat-containing umbilical hernia. No pathologically enlarged lymph nodes in the retroperitoneum or mesentery. Atherosclerotic changes in the abdominal aorta and its branches. No hydronephrosis. Bilateral multiple renal hypodensities, some too small to be characterized. A large renal cyst in the interpolar region of the left kidney, measuring 5.7 x 5.3 cm. The appendix is enlarged measuring 9-11 mm, fluid-filled, with enhancing wall and minimal fat stranding. No free fluid in the pelvis. The urinary bladder, seminal vesicles, and prostate appear within normal limits. Bilateral small fat-containing inguinal hernias. No suspicious lytic or sclerotic lesions are seen.
